<br>
See, this is actually where we differ.  I was playing this game when it was first released as well.  What you refer to as &quot;dumbing down&quot;, I like to think of as enhancing.  EQ has a very steep learning curve compared to the majority of computer games out there.  Things like no corpse runs below lvl 10, larger quantities of food/water to begin with,  pop up learning tips, newbie quest armors, PoK books etc don't &quot;dumb down&quot; the game.  They just lower some of the downtime learning the basics, travel time, corpse run time etc.  Lowering down time for beginers to EQ is a good thing.  I remember how traumatic it was for me when I was a lowly lvl 6 mage (a character long since deleted) and I lost my corpse in lesser faydark.  It took me (and I'm not exagerating) about 6 hours to find my damn corpse.  Now bear in mind that my PC was subpar back then, and the majority of the time I played it was necessary for me to use the top down view due to lag especially in cities.  I could actually navigate the majority of pre-kunark zones looking at my feet.  But I loved the concept of the game so much that I would play it anyway.  I can say with some confidence that most sane people wouldn't put themselves through that.  Is SoE trying to make this game more enjoyable to people new to the game? Absolutely.  But it's from feedback from players like me that found many aspects of old-school EQ as Bs.  So yes.  They are trying to get new customers by listening to their older ones.  They are also making changes that affect me as a lvl 65 char as well.<br>
<br>
Oh.. and no I don't believe their target audience is players incapable of tieing their own shoes.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaman>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 3501<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/03 12:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> &gt;Oh.. and no I don't believe their target audience is players incapable of tieing their own shoes. <br>
