<br>
As for WoW: I agree that Blizzard makes cool games and that they are relatively bug free. Their biggest problem is and always has been hacking / cheating on Battlenet servers. They really must address that issue if they want to be successful. Another thing is class balance and overall game playability. They have never done a MORG, so it's illogical to assume that their MORG will be better then all others, just because. Further, they must address caster vrs. melee balance, sense of accomplishment vrs. privately generated dungeons, mudflation, balance between early, mid and high end game, and a host of other factors that don't particulary matter in Warcraft 3 (for example).<br>
<br>
I ain't knocking them, but put the pipe down and think about what a daunting task doing all of that right enough to &quot;work&quot; is gonna be. Now imagine how hard it will be to do it better then EQ, which has the benefit of YEARS of practice, tweaking, etc. I hope WoW is amazing, because I like the setting, but assuming that it will totally bury EQ is hilariously naive, to say the least.<br>
